==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: -nik
<hw>-nik</hw> <pr>(n⟦icr⟧k)</pr> <pos>suff.</pos> <ety>[Yiddish, fr.
Slavik suffix <ets>-nik</ets> indicating a person.]</ety> <def>A suffix
attached to other words indicating <sig>a person with certain
characteristics</sig> or associated with a certain group or behavior;
<as>as, beat<ex>nik</ex>, kibbutz<ex>nik</ex></as>; it is sometimes used
derogatorily; <as>as in no-good<ex>nik</ex>,
peace<ex>nik</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

